ite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=amazonprincessraven>Amazon Princess Raven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/23/01 1:36:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> TRV Fireside</span><hr size=1> THe moon was lit high above the Valley. Earlier that day, Raven and a few of the archers went into the forests and caught a few deer for the fireside ceremony. <br>
<br>
The meat and other foods had been gathered and layed out upon a long table in the center of the village. A large fire was being built by the Princess herself as other amazons cleared out the village so as others could dance and make merry if they wished.<br>
<br>
Raven leaned down making sure no one was watching, and her hand gently touched one of the bundles of sticks around the fire, and they lit instantly burning brightly.<br>
<br>
She turned and clapped her hands together high over her head.<br>
<br>
&quot;Come sisters! Gather the food and the drink. For tonight we celebrate the harvest moon, and birth of my sister. Glory!&quot;<br>
<br>
The others with her cheered lightly and began to set out the goblets and chalices for those who were left to come. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonqueenyakut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/30/01 6:15:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TRV Fireside</span><hr size=1> Yakut emerged from her hut with baby Glory in her arms. A smile on her face as she appoarched her beloved Raven. The child was bundled in a shaman robes. All of Yakut's children were shamans. <br>
<br>
&quot;Yasoo, Raven.&quot;<br>
<br>
She placed a kiss on her eldest daughter's forehead.<br>
<br>
&quot;M'dear, do you wish to hold your young sister?&quot;<br>
<br>
 <p>§-:¦:-§ Yakut §-:¦:-§

Amazon Queen, Amazon Shamaness, and Amazon Mother...Your good old Northern Amazon!
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugloryoftrv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glory of TRV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/30/01 9:20:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TRV Fireside</span><hr size=1> Glory bes all bundled up in mommys arms. <br>
<br>
Not being fussy.....yet. Curious little eyes dance around at the sky and everything around her as she gums one of her tiny lil fists,getting drool all over her lil hand and tiny lil chin.<br>
<br>
She pulls her fist out of her toothless lil mouth and raises both tiny lil fist up skyward and shakes them about. &quot;Goo gah!&quot; Then she resumes gumming that lil fist again,while her other hand finds a leather string hanging from mommy Yakuts shamaness robe and clutches the leather bit in that tiny hand and lightly tugs on it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://hometown.aol.com/princessglory/images/babyglory1.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=amazonprincessraven>Amazon Princess Raven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/31/01 1:17:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Glory</span><hr size=1> Raven turned. Paint had already been placed under her eyes. Her eyes were already glowing black as the moon was in it's highest aura.<br>
<br>
She looked down at the child and sighed turning away from her Mother's kiss.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'd better not.&quot;<br>
<br>
She walked more towards the fire and spoke in the Northern tongue that Yakut could understand.<br>
<br>
*&quot;Ancients, help me harness the darkness inside of me.&quot;*<br>
<br>
Most had forgotten the curse of Raven. She was immortal . . .  a Goddess and a dark one at that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ufaithamznprincess21.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FaithAmznPrincess21</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/3/02 7:36:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TRV Fireside</span><hr size=1> :appears:<br>
Yasoo princess, queen.<br>
I arrive just yesterday in the village. sees the baby. :smiles:<br>
and to give Glory this. :hands Glory a necklace:when she is old enough give it to her. its for all amazon sisters that she knows and that love her. <br>
<br>
:steps back: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonqueenyakut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/6/02 6:57:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TRV Fireside</span><hr size=1> Yakut sighed listening to her daughters words. The curse was someting Yakut took on as her fault. She loved her daughter Raven and knew that she, if ever Yakut died, would be the one to become Queen. It was her destiny to take Yakut's place. Though Glory and Lynn were Amazon Princesses (Lynn was dead she back but she wont be in this post) and could become Queen, it was Raven who would rule first. Raven being the eldest daughter. She laid a hand on her daughters shoulder from behind.<br>
<br>
&quot;Raven, always remember no matter what, I love you. You are my daughter and beautiful. You are the next ruler of the Valley, and you shall do well. I am so sorry. I let a dark god of unkown ways take away your childhood. Its my fault. I seek forgiveness for doing this to you.&quot; <p>§-:¦:-§ Yakut §-:¦:-§

Amazon Queen, Amazon Shamaness, and Amazon Mother...Your good old Northern Amazon!
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=amazonprincessraven>Amazon Princess Raven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/6/02 11:37:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A sigh</span><hr size=1> Raven lightly pushed her mother's hand away from her shoulder.<br>
<br>
&quot;Mother, don't be weak. Appologies are for those who need others. Besides, it wasn't your fault.&quot;<br>
<br>
She held her hand outward towards the fire and it blazed upwards lightly.<br>
<br>
&quot;I love my life.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonqueenyakut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/8/02 5:32:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A sigh</span><hr size=1> Yakut just sighed and cradled young Glory. Raven was much different from Yakut and she saw it clearly but it still hurt to see her daughter turn away from her. Yakut stared into the fire and runs the memory of Raven's birth through her head. It was a stormy night when Raven was brought into the world. Yakut remembered every detail. Yakut had chosen Raven a pair of godsmothers incase anything happened to her. She never told her daughter of them, simply because she knew Raven wouldn't need them. Yakut's wacthed as the Flames danced about wildy, in her own world of memory lane. <p>§-:¦:-§ Yakut §-:¦:-§

Amazon Queen, Amazon Shamaness, and Amazon Mother...Your good old Northern Amazon!
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonqueenyakut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/8/02 5:35:00 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uchristannagoddessofpeace.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Christanna Goddess of Peace</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/12/02 2:33:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A sigh</span><hr size=1> Christanna made her way into TRV, she had been missing Yakut and remembered that she was the Queen of this valley. She saw Yakut looking very sad over by the fireside, and walked over to her and sat down beside her, putting a hand gently on her shoulder.<br>
<br>
~Hello Yakut... what's the matter?~ she asked, looking into her eyes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonqueenyakut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/13/02 8:33:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Christanna YAY!</span><hr size=1> Yakut looked over to Tanna and smiled brightly. Yakut gave Christanna a hug after the embrace she returned her eyes to Tanna.<br>
<br>
&quot;Greetings Christanna, its nothing really. how are you?&quot;<br>
<br>
She gets a tiny bit thirsty.<br>
<br>
&quot;Care for a drink? I'm sure KaLi would be able to retrieve anything you want. What do think of my little home here in the Valley?&quot; <p>§-:¦:-§ Yakut §-:¦:-§

Amazon Queen, Amazon Shamaness, and Amazon Mother...Your good old Northern Amazon!
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uchristannagoddessofpeace.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Christanna Goddess of Peace</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/14/02 9:31:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Christanna YAY!</span><hr size=1> ~Tanna turned and smiled~ I am not thirsty, thank you Yakut... and I think your home is beautiful... I wonder which of these Amazons is your daughter? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonqueenyakut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/14/02 9:36:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Christanna YAY!</span><hr size=1> She smiles at the mention of her daughters.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, the one by the fire who has a odd darkness about her is Raven my eldest daughter. Glory is in my arms here. and Lynn is my adopted daughter she is the one sitting next to that other shaman over there.&quot;<br>
<br>
To each daughters position she nodded towards.<br>
<br>
&quot;Would you like to meet them?&quot; <br>
<br>
She looked at Raven then whispered in Christanna ear.<br>
<br>
&quot;Becareful, Raven doesn't take to gods that easy.&quot; <p>§-:¦:-§ Yakut §-:¦:-§

Amazon Queen, Amazon Shamaness, and Amazon Mother...Your good old Northern Amazon!
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uchristannagoddessofpeace.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Christanna Goddess of Peace</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/14/02 9:38:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Christanna YAY!</span><hr size=1> Christanna smiled at little Glory and tickled her chin. She looked back to Yakut and nodded. ~Yes, I'd very much like to meet them... and if Raven does not like me because I am a goddess, that is all right...~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonqueenyakut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/15/02 7:57:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Infamous Daughters of Yakut</span><hr size=1> Yakut stood up and took Christanna by the wrist walking her to Raven, Yakut's first and eldest daughter. She tapped Raven on the shoulder lightly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Raven, I have someone I want you to meet.&quot;<br>
<br>
She clasped Tanna's hand in between her own two and smiled brightly.<br>
<br>
&quot;This is Christanna Goddess of Peace. She is a... friend of mine.&quot;<br>
<br>
In the short time Yakut had known Christanna, she had fell in love with the beautiful goddess. She worried that Raven would be enraged by the fact her mother loved a Goddess but she hoped Raven could accept it... for her. <p>§-:¦:-§ Yakut §-:¦:-§

Amazon Queen, Amazon Shamaness, and Amazon Mother...Your good old Northern Amazon!
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uprincesslynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Princess Lynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/15/02 8:35:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Infamous Daughters of Yakut</span><hr size=1> Lynn is sitting down, looking closely at the rage of the fire, that shine through out the tribe in the dark night. Lynn does a small sigh as she sits there alone.(i know someone is sitting next to her, but she means alone in family way). Lynn looks over to her mother, Yakut, and then the stranger Goddess that has come. Lynn quirks a brow not knowing who this woman is. Lynn stands and walks to Yakut....she stands behind yakut, her friend and raven. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uchristannagoddessofpeace.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Christanna Goddess of Peace</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/15/02 9:21:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The infamous daughters of Yakut</span><hr size=1> Christanna smiled sweetly at Raven, and a little shiver ran through her body as Yakut took her hand in hers. She sensed a presence behind her and turned to see a young Amazon standing there, looking curiously at her. ~Hi,~ she said softly, tugging on Yakut's arm a bit to catch her attention to the young girl. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugloryoftrv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glory of TRV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/16/02 3:03:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The infamous daughters of Yakut</span><hr size=1> Glory pulls her lil fist out of her toothless mouth and looks up at Christanna curiously.<br>
<br>
